snippet: The second round of negotiations on a nuclear agreement with Iran is set to begin Tuesday and success hinges on solidarity among the members of the United Nations Security Council.
abstract: Tensions between the West and Russia over events in Ukraine could disrupt second round of negotiations set to begin in Vienna on permanent nuclear agreement with Iran; success of the talks hinges on solidarity among five permanent members of the United Nations Security Council, which includes Russia.
lead_paragraph: The second round of negotiations on a nuclear agreement with Iran is set to begin Tuesday and success hinges on solidarity among the members of the United Nations Security Council.

headline.main: Deterioration in U.S.-Russian Relations May Disrupt Coming Talks With Iran
headline.print_headline: Deterioration in U.S.-Russian Relations May Disrupt Coming Talks With Iran
